Silver-gilt; lobed ovoid body and cover supported by a stem in the shape of a tree trunk with figure of a woodman

Silver-gilt; the spreading circular silver-gilt foot is embossed with a ring of lobes round a central dome, which supports the silver stem in the shape of a tree trunk encircled by a creeper, and the figure of an ax-wielding woodman.  The ovoid silver-gilt body and interlocking cover are embossed with lobes.  The silver finial is formed as a bunch of flowers.
